# 🧭 IT Onboarding Knowledge Base

This Knowledge Base (KB) provides standardized IT onboarding procedures for new employees within the organization.  
It ensures consistent device setup, system access, and compliance with IT security standards.

---

## 🧩 1. Onboarding Overview

**Objective:**  
To successfully onboard new employees with all required IT access, ensuring compliance, productivity, and data security.

**Key Responsibilities:**
- IT Support Officer – Setup & configuration
- HR – Employee identity confirmation
- New Employee – Account verification & MDM enrollment

---

## 🧠 2. Pre-Onboarding Checklist

| Item | Description | Responsible | Status |
|------|--------------|--------------|---------|
| Email account creation | Create user mailbox and assign license | IT Admin | ✅ |
| AD user setup | Create AD profile and assign group policy | IT Admin | ✅ |
| MDM readiness | Confirm device meets Intune/MDM requirements | IT Support | ✅ |
| Hardware allocation | Assign laptop or VM | HR/IT | ✅ |

---

## 🧰 3. Device Setup & MDM Enrollment

**Steps:**
1. Log into Windows using temporary credentials.  
2. Navigate to:  
   `Settings → Accounts → Access work or school → Connect`
3. Enter work email (e.g. first.last@company.com)
4. Follow on-screen instructions to complete enrollment.

**Screenshot:**
![MDM Enrollment Screenshot](./screenshots/mdm_enrollment.png)

---

## 🖥️ 4. Virtual Machine Setup (Win10_MasterImage Example)

| Setting | Configuration |
|----------|----------------|
| VM Name | Win10_MasterImage |
| Generation | 2 |
| Startup Memory | 4096 MB |
| Network | Default Switch |
| Installation Media | Windows 11 ISO |

**Screenshot:**
![VM Summary Screenshot](./screenshots/vm_summary.png)

---

## 🧾 5. Account & Access Configuration

- Assign M365 license and Teams access  
- Add user to appropriate AD group  
- Enable MFA on first login  
- Configure email signature and password policy

**Screenshot:**
![Account Setup Screenshot](./screenshots/account_setup.png)

